obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (2389)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2389&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Rubber^1*** Act, 1947.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2[except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*.]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The brackets and words "(Production and Marketing)" omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "except Part B States" (w.e.f. 1-4-1951).`
  line
  line `*. Vide Notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (2390)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration as to expediency of Union control.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1954, s. 4, for section 2 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2390&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `^1[2. Declaration as to expediency of Union control.--It is hereby declared that it is expedient in the`
  line `public interest that the Union should take under its control the rubber industry.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (2391)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2391&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Board" means the ^1*** Rubber Board constituted under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "dealer", means any person who deals in rubber, whether wholesale or retail, or holds stocks`
  line `of rubber, and includes the representative or agent of a dealer;`
  line
  line `(c) "estate" means any area administered as one unit which contains land planted with rubber`
  line plants;
  line
  line `^2[(cc) "Executive Director" means the Executive Director appointed under this Act;]`
  line
  line `(d) "export" and "import" mean respectively taking out of, and bringing into ^3[India] by sea, land`
  line `or air;`
  line
  line `^4[(dd) "India" means the territory of India excluding the State of Jammu and Kashmir*;]`
  line
  line `(e) "manufacturer" means any person engaged in the manufacture of any article in the making of`
  line `which rubber is used;`
  line
  line `(f) "owner" includes any agent of an owner and a mortgagee in possession and a lessee of an`
  line estate;
  line
  line `(g) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `^5[(ga) "processor" means a person who undertakes the processing of rubber;]`
  line
  line `(h) "rubber" means--`
  line
  line `(i) crude rubber, that is to say, rubber prepared from the leaves, bark or latex of any rubber`
  line plant;
  line
  line `(ii) the latex of any rubber plant whether fluid or coagulated, in any stage of the treatment to`
  line `which it is subjected during the process of conversion into rubber;`
  line
  line `(iii) latex (dry rubber content) in any state of concentration,`
  line
  line `and includes scrap rubber, sheet rubber, rubber in powder and all forms and varieties of crepe rubber, but`
  line `does not include rubber contained in any manufactured article;`
  line
  line `(i) "rubber plant" includes plants, trees, shrubs or vines of any of the following:--`
  line
  line `(i) Hevea Braziliensis (Para Rubber),`
  line
  line `(ii) Manihot Glaziovii (Ceara Rubber),`
  line
  line `(iii) Castillio elastica,`
  line
  line `(iv) Ficus elastica (Rambong), and`
  line
  line `(v) any other plant which the Board may, by notification in the Gazette of India, declare to be`
  line `a rubber plant for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) "Rubber Production Commissioner" means the Rubber Production Commissioner appointed`
  line `under this Act;`
  line
  line `^6[(k) "small grower" means an owner whose estate does not exceed ^7[fifty acres] in area.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "Indian" omitted by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `2. The words in brackets shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by Act 54 of 1982, s. 2.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "the States" (w.e.f. 1-4-1951).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 3 and Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f.1-4-1951).`
  line
  line `5. The words in brackets shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by Act 4 of 2010, s. 2.`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 54 of 1954, s. 5 (w.e.f 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `7. The words in brackets shall stand substituted (date to be notified) by Act 4 of 2010, s. 2, for "ten hectares".`
  line
  line `*. Vide Notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (2392)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Constitution of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2392&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) As soon as may be after the commencement of this Act, the`
  line `Central Government shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, constitute for the purposes of this Act a`
  line `Board to be called the ^1*** Rubber Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall be a body corporate by the name of ^1*** Rubber Board having perpetual`
  line `succession and a common seal with power to acquire and hold property, both movable and immovable`
  line `and to contract, and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) The Board shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairman to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `^3[(b) two members to represent the State of ^4[Tamil Nadu], one of whom shall be a person`
  line `representing rubber producing interests;`
  line
  line `(c) eight members to represent the State of Kerala, six of whom shall be persons representing the`
  line `rubber producing interests, three of such six being persons representing the small growers;]`
  line
  line `(d) ten members to be nominated by the Central Government, of whom two shall represent the`
  line `manufacturers and four labours;`
  line
  line `^5[(da) three members to be nominated by the Central Government of whom two shall be from the`
  line `Department of Commerce and one from the Department of Agriculture and Co-operation;]`
  line
  line `(e) three members of Parliament of whom two shall be elected by the House of the People and`
  line `one by the Council of States; ^6[and]`
  line
  line `^7[(ee) the Executive Director, ex officio; and]`
  line
  line `(f) the Rubber Production Commissioner, ex officio.`
  line
  line `(4) The persons to represent the States of ^8[Tamil Nadu] and ^9[Kerala] shall be elected or nominated`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) Any officer of the Central Government when deputed by that Government in this behalf shall have`
  line `the right to attend the meetings of the Board and take part in the proceedings thereof but shall not be`
  line `entitled to vote.`
  line
  line `(6) The Board shall elect from among its members a Vice-Chairman who shall exercise such of the`
  line `powers, and perform such of the functions of the Chairman as may be prescribed or as may be delegated`
  line `to him by the Chairman.`
  line
  line `(7) The members of the Board shall receive from the Board such allowances as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(8) It is hereby declared that the office of member of the Board shall not disqualify its holder for`
  line `being chosen as, or for being, a member of either House of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "Indian" omitted by Act 54 of 1954, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for sub-sections (3), (4) and (5) (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Adaption of Laws (No. 3) Order, 1956, clauses (b) and (c).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the Madras State (Alteration of Name) (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subject) Order, 1970, for "Madras"`
  line `(w.e.f. 14-1-1969).`
  line
  line `5. The words in brackets shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by Act 4 of 2010, s. 3.`
  line
  line `6. The word "and" shall stand omitted (date to be notified) by Act 54 of 1982, s. 3.`
  line
  line `7. The words in brackets shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by s. 3, ibid.`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by the Madras State (Alteration of Name) (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) 1970, for "Madras"`
  line `(w.e.f. 14-1-1969).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Adaptation of Laws (No. 3) Order, 1956, for "Travancore-Cochin".`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (2393)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Vacancies in the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2393&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any authority or body fails to make within a reasonable time any`
  line `nomination which it is entitled to make under section 4, the Central Government may itself nominate a`
  line `member to fill the vacancy.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a member of the Board dies, resigns or is removed, or ceases to reside in India, or becomes`
  line
  line `incapable of acting, the Central Government shall, on the recommendation of the authority or body`
  line `entitled to nominate the member under section 4, or where such recommendation is not made within a`
  line `reasonable time, then on its own initiative, appoint a person to fill the vacancy.`
  line
  line `(3) No act done by the Board shall be questioned on the ground merely of the existence of any`
  line `vacancy in, or defect in the constitution of the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (2394)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Salary and allowances of Chairman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2394&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[6. Salary and allowances of Chairman.--^2[The Chairman] shall be entitled to such salary and`
  line `allowances and be governed by such conditions of service in respect of leave, pension, provident fund and`
  line `other matters as may from time to time be fixed by the Central Government ^3[and a person appointed as`
  line `the part-time Chairman shall be entitled to such honorarium and allowances, if any, and such other`
  line `conditions of service as may from time to time be fixed by the Central Government].]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1954, s. 7, for section 6 (w.e.f 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `2. The words in brackets shall stand substituted (date to be notified) by Act 54 of 1982, s. 4 to read as "A person appointed as the`
  line `whole-time Chairman" .`
  line
  line `3. The words in brackets shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by s. 4, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_a:
  sectionId (2395)
  sectionNo 6A
  orderNo 7
  title `Executive Officers of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2395&sectionno=6A&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[6A. Executive Officers of the Board.--^2[(1) The Central Government may appoint an Executive`
  line `Director to exercise such powers and perform such duties under the direction of the Board as may be`
  line `prescribed or as may be delegated to him by the Chairman.]`
  line
  line `^3[(1A)] The Central Government shall appoint a Rubber Production Commissioner to exercise such`
  line `powers and perform such duties under the direction of the Board as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall appoint a Secretary to the Board to exercise such powers and`
  line `perform such duties under the direction of the Board as may be prescribed or as may be delegated to him`
  line `by the Chairman.`
  line
  line `(3)`
  line `^4[The Rubber Production Commissioner] and the Secretary to the Board shall be entitled to such`
  line `salaries and allowances and be governed by such conditions of service regarding leave, pension, provident`
  line `fund and other matters as may be fixed by the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `(4)`
  line `^5[The Chairman,] the Rubber Production Commissioner and the Secretary shall not undertake any`
  line `work unconnected with their duties under this Act except with the permission of the Central`
  line Government.]
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1954, s. 7, for section 6 (w.e.f 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `2. The words in brackets shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by s. 5, ibid.`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (1) shall renumbered as sub-section (1A) thereof (date to be notified) by s. 5, ibid.`
  line
  line `4. The words in brackets shall stand substituted (date to be notified) by s. 5, ibid. to read as "the Executive Directors, the Rubber`
  line `Production Commissioner"`
  line
  line `5. The word in brackets shall stand substituted (date to be notified) by 54 of 1982, s. 5, to read as "Chairman, if whole-time, the`
  line `Executive Director"`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (2396)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Committees of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2396&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^1* * * *`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may appoint such ^2*** Committees as may be necessary for the efficient performance`
  line `of its duties and functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall have the power to co-opt as members of any Committee appointed under`
  line `sub-section (2) such number of persons who are not members of the Board, as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board may appoint and authorize agents to discharge on its behalf any of its functions in`
  line `relation to the marketing or storing of rubber.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Omitted by Act 54 of 1954, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `2. The word "other" omitted by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (2397)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Functions of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2397&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the Board to promote by such measures as it`
  line `thinks fit the development of the rubber industry ^1***.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provision, the measures referred to therein`
  line `may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) undertaking, assisting or encouraging scientific, technological and economic research;`
  line
  line `(b) training students in improved methods of planting, cultivation, manuring and spraying;`
  line
  line `(c) the supply of technical advice to rubber growers;`
  line
  line `(d) improving the marketing of rubber;`
  line
  line `^2[(da) improving the quality of rubber and implementing the standards for quality marking,`
  line `labeling and packing for the rubber produced or processed in, imported into or exported from, India;]`
  line
  line `(e) the collection of statistics from owners of estates, dealers, ^3[and manufacturers];`
  line
  line `^4[(f) securing better working conditions and the provisions and improvement of amenities and`
  line `incentives for workers;`
  line
  line `(g) carrying out any other duties which may be vested in the Board under rules made under this`
  line Act.]
  line
  line `(3) It shall also be the duty of the Board--`
  line
  line `(a) to advise the Central Government on all matters relating to the development of the rubber`
  line `industry, including the import and export of rubber;`
  line
  line `(b) to advice the Central Government with regard to participation in any international Conference`
  line `or scheme relating to rubber;`
  line
  line `(c) to submit to the Central Government and such other authorities as may be prescribed`
  line `^5[half-yearly reports] on its activities and the working of this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) to prepare and furnish such other reports relating to the rubber industry as may be required by`
  line `the Central Government from time to time.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "so far as regards the production and marketing of rubber" omitted by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `2. The words in brackets shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by Act 4 of 2010, s. 4.`
  line
  line `3. The words in brackets shall stand substituted (date to be notified) by s. 4, ibid., to read as "manufactures and processors"`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 54 of 1954, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `5. The words in brackets shall stand substituted (date to be notified) by Act 4 of 2010, s. 4 to read as "annual report".`
obj_root_law_sections_8_a:
  sectionId (2398)
  sectionNo 8A
  orderNo 10
  title `Power of the Board to import rubber for sale, or to purchase rubber in the internal market.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 54 of 1954, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2398&sectionno=8A&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[8A. Power of the Board to import rubber for sale, or to purchase rubber, in the internal`
  line `market.--It shall be lawful for the Board with the previous approval of the Central Government to import rubber for sale, or to purchase rubber, in the internal market at such prices as the Central`
  line `Government may fix.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_b:
  sectionId (2399)
  sectionNo 8B
  orderNo 11
  title `Consultation with the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 54 of 1954, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2399&sectionno=8B&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_8_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[8B. Consultation with the Board.--Before taking any action touching the affairs of the Board under`
  line `this Act, the Central Government shall ordinarily consult the Board:]`
  line
  line `Provided that no action taken by the Central Government shall be invalid or called in question merely`
  line `on the ground that the action was taken without such consultation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (2400)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 12
  title `Funds of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2400&sectionno=9&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[9. Funds of the Board.--(1) The Indian Rubber Production Board constituted under the Rubber`
  line `Control and Production Order, 1946, is hereby dissolved, and all funds and other property vested in, and`
  line `all liabilities of, that Board shall respectively vest in, and be liabilities of, the Board constituted under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `^2[(2) The Board shall maintain two funds, a general fund and a pool fund.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Sections 9, 9A and 9B shall stand substituted (date to be notified) by Act 4 of 2010, s. 5 to read us under:`
  line
  line `"[9. Rubber Development Fund.--"(1) There shall be a fund to be called the Rubber Development Fund and there shall be`
  line credited,--
  line
  line `(a) all sums forming the funds of the Board immediately before the commencement of the Rubber (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 2009;`
  line
  line `(b) the proceeds of cess paid to the Board by the Central Government under sub-section (7) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(c) any sum of money that may be paid to the Board by way of grants or loans by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(d) internal and extra budgetary resources of the Board;`
  line
  line `(e) all moneys received and collected under section 26A; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other sum that may be levied and collected under this Act and the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) The Rubber Development Fund shall be applied--`
  line
  line `(a) to meet the expenses of the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) to meet the cost of the measures referred to in section 8;`
  line
  line `(c) to meet the expenditure incurred in the performance of its functions under this Act or the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(d) to meet the expenditure for rehabilitation of small growers; and`
  line
  line `(e) for making such grants to rubber estates or for meeting the cost of such other assistance to rubber estates as the`
  line `Board may think necessary for the development of such estates.".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 54 of 1954, s. 11, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_a:
  sectionId (2401)
  sectionNo 9A
  orderNo 13
  title `General fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-1955)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2401&sectionno=9A&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[9A. General fund.--(1) To the general fund shall be credited--`
  line
  line `(a) all sums forming the funds of the Board immediately before the commencement of the Rubber`
  line `(Production and Marketing) Amendment Act, 1954 (54 of 1954);`
  line
  line `(b) all amounts paid to the Board by the Central Government under sub-section (7) of section 12.`
  line
  line `(2) The general fund shall be applied--`
  line
  line `(a) to meet the expenses of the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) to meet the costs of the measures referred to in section 8;`
  line
  line `(c) to meet the expenditure incurred in the performance of its functions under this Act or under`
  line `rules made thereunder; and`
  line
  line `(d) for making such grants to rubber estates or for meeting the cost of such other assistance to`
  line `rubber estates as the Board may think necessary for the development of such estates.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_b:
  sectionId (2402)
  sectionNo 9B
  orderNo 14
  title `Pool fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-1955)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2402&sectionno=9B&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_9_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[9B. Pool fund.--(1) To the pool fund shall be credited--`
  line
  line `(a) all sums realized by sales of rubber imported or purchased under section 8A;`
  line
  line `(b) any other sum which the Board may, with the previous approval of the Central Government,`
  line `transfer from the general fund to the pool fund.`
  line
  line `(2) The pool fund shall be applied only to the rehabilitation of small growers in such manner as may`
  line `be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (2403)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 15
  title Registration.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2403&sectionno=10&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `^1[10. Registration.--(1) Every person owning land planted with rubber plants, whether such land is`
  line `comprised in one estate or in more than one estate and whether it is situated wholly or only partly in`
  line `^2[India], shall, before the expiry of one month from the date of commencement of this Act, apply to the`
  line `Board to be registered as an owner in respect of each estate owned by him.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 10 shall stand omitted (date to be notified) by Act 4 of 2010, s. 6.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "the States" (w.e.f. 1-4-1951)`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (2404)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power to prohibit or control imports and exports of rubber.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2404&sectionno=11&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `may,^1*** by order published in the Official Gazette, make provision for prohibiting, restricting or`
  line `otherwise controlling the import or export of rubber, either generally or in specified classes of cases.`
  line
  line `(2) All goods to which any order under sub-section (1) applies shall be deemed to be goods of which`
  line `the import or export has been prohibited or restricted under section 19 of the Sea Customs Act, 1878`
  line `(8 of 1878), and all the provisions of that Act shall have effect accordingly, except that section 183`
  line `thereof shall have effect as if for the word "shall" therein the word "may" were substituted.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person contravenes any order made under sub-section (1) he shall, without prejudice to any`
  line `confiscation or penalty to which he may be liable under the provisions of the Sea Customs Act, 1878 (8 of 1978), as applied by sub-section (2), be punishable with ^2[penalty which may extend to one lakh rupees or cancellation of licence issued under section 14, or with both]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "after consulting the Boar" omitted by Act 54 of 1954, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `2.. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for certain words (w.e.f. 9-8-2024).`
  line .
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (2405)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 17
  title `Imposition of new rubber cess.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2405&sectionno=12&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[12. Imposition of new rubber cess.--(1) With effect from such date as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint, there shall be levied as a cess for the purposes of this`
  line `Act, a duty of excise on all rubber produced in India at such rate, not exceeding ^2[two rupees] per`
  line `kilogram of rubber so produced, as the Central Government may fix.`
  line
  line `(2) The duty of excise levied under sub-section (1) shall be collected by the Board in accordance with`
  line `rules made in this behalf either from the owner of the estate on which the rubber is produced or from the`
  line `manufacturer by whom ^3[such rubber is used.]`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that the Central Government may, if considered necessary in the public interest, by order`
  line `for reasons to be recorded in writing, exempt or reduce the duty of excise on rubber exported on such`
  line `terms and conditions as it deems fit:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify`
  line `zero paisa per kilogram as the rate of duty of excise on natural rubber produced in India and procured for`
  line `export by the exporters of natural rubber for the period from the 1st April, 1961 to the 31st August, 2003.]`
  line
  line `^5[(3) The owner or, as the case may be, the manufacturer shall pay to the Board the amount of the`
  line `duty within one month from the date on which he receives a notice of demand therefor from the Board`
  line `and, if he fails to do so, the duty may be recovered from the owner or the manufacturer, as the case may`
  line `be, as an arrear of land revenue.]`
  line
  line `(4) For the purpose of enabling the Board to assess the amount of the duty of excise levied under this`
  line section--
  line
  line `(a) the Board shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, fix a period in respect of which`
  line `assessments shall be made; and`
  line
  line `(b) without prejudice to the provisions of section 20, every owner and every manufacturer shall`
  line `furnish to the Board a return not later than ^6[fifteen days] after the expiry of the period to which the`
  line `return relates, stating,--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of an owner, the total quantity of rubber produced on the estate in each such`
  line `period:`
  line
  line `Provided that in respect of an estate situated only partly in India, the owner shall in the said`
  line `return show separately the quantity of rubber produced within and outside India;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of a manufacturer, the total quantity of ^7[rubber used] by him in such period`
  line `out of the rubber produced in India.`
  line
  line `(5) if any ^8[owner or manufacturer] fails to furnish, within the time prescribed, the return referred to`
  line `in sub-section (4) or furnishes a return which the Board has reason to believe is incorrect or defective, the`
  line `Board may assess the amount of the duty of excise in such manner as may be prescribed ^9[and collect the`
  line `cess from the owner, exporter or the manufacturer, as the case may be, after issuing a notice and after`
  line `making such enquiry as it considers necessary, with such rate of interest as fixed under sub-section (3):`
  line
  line `Provided that where for any reason, the Board finds that an owner, exporter or manufacturer, as the`
  line `case may be, has paid cess in excess of what is due from him, it shall be adjusted against the future`
  line `payment, if any, from him or shall be refunded to him.]`
  line
  line `(6) Any person aggrieved by an assessment made under this section may, within three months of the`
  line `service of the notice under sub-section (3), apply to the District Judge for the cancellation or modification`
  line `of the assessment, and the District Judge shall, after giving the Board an opportunity of being heard, pass`
  line `such order (which shall be final) as he thinks proper.`
  line
  line `(7) The proceeds of the duty of excise collected under this section reduced by the cost of collection as`
  line `determined by the Central Government shall first be credited to the Consolidated Fund of India, and then`
  line `be paid by the Central Government to the Board for being utilised for the purposes of this Act, if`
  line `Parliament by appropriation made by law in this behalf so provides.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 1960, s. 2, for section 12 (w.e.f. 1-11-1960).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 1994, s. 2, for "fifty naye paise" (w.e.f. 19-5-1994).`
  line
  line `3. The words in brackets shall stand substituted (date to be notified) by Act 4 of 2010, s. 7 to read as under`
  line `"such rubber is used or from the exporter by whom such rubber is exported"`
  line
  line `4. The provisions shall stand substituted (date to be notified) by s. 7, ibid.`
  line
  line `5. Sub-section (3) shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by s. 7, ibid. to read as under:`
  line
  line `"(3) Subject to the provisions of this Act, every owner, exporter or the manufacturer, as the case may be, shall pay the duty`
  line `of excise to the Board in the manner and for the period referred to in sub-section (4) and, if he fails to do so, the duty may be`
  line `recovered with the cost of collection and interest at such rates, as may be prescribed, from the owner, exporter or the`
  line `manufacturer, as the case may be, as an arrear of the land revenue.".`
  line
  line `6. The words in brackets shall stand substituted (date to be notified) by Act 4 of 2010, s. 7 to read as "thirty days"`
  line
  line `7. The words in brackets shall stand substituted (date to be notified) by s. 7, ibid., to read as "rubber acquired"`
  line
  line `8. The words in brackets shall stand substituted (date to be notified) by s. 7, ibid., to read as "owner, exporter or manufacturer"`
  line
  line `9. The words, brackets and figure in brackets shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by s. 7, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (2406)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to fix maximum and minimum prices for sale of rubber.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2406&sectionno=13&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `may ^1, if it deems necessary, ^2*** by order published in the official Gazette, fix the maximum price or`
  line `the minimum price or the maximum and minimum prices to be charged, in the course of a business of any`
  line `class specified in the order, for rubber of any description so specified.`
  line
  line `(2) Any such order may fix different maximum or minimum prices to be charged in the course of`
  line `businesses of different classes for the same description of rubber.`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words in brackets shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by s. 8, ibid.`
  line
  line `2. The words, brackets and figures "after consulting the Rubber Price Advisory Committee constituted under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 7" omitted by Act 54 of 1954, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (3) omitted by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 9-8-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (2407)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 19
  title `Licensing of transactions in rubber.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Proviso omitted by Act 50 of 1949, s. 2 (w.e.f. 8-12-1949).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2407&sectionno=14&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `No person shall sell or otherwise dispose of and no`
  line `person shall buy or otherwise acquire, rubber except under and in accordance with the terms of a general`
  line `or special licence issued by the Board:`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (2408)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 20
  title `Provisions regarding licences under section 14.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2408&sectionno=15&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every general licence issued under`
  line `section 14 shall be published by the Board in the Gazette of India and in such newspapers as the Board`
  line `may direct.`
  line
  line `(2) A special licence issued under section 14 shall be valid only for such period as may be specified`
  line `therein:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board may from time to time extend the period of validity of any such licence.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may at any time for reasons to be recorded by it in writing revoke a special licence`
  line `granted under section 14, and on such revocation it shall be returned to the Board by the person to whom`
  line `it was issued.`
  line
  line `(4) No application for a special licence made by a person who was carrying on business as a dealer or`
  line `manufacturer immediately before the commencement of this Act shall be rejected by the Board except for`
  line `special reasons to be recorded in writing.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (2409)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 21
  title `Restriction on possession of rubber.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2409&sectionno=16&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person not being the owner or occupant of an`
  line `estate or a person who has acquired rubber under a general or special licence issued by the Board under`
  line `section 14 shall have any rubber in his possession.`
  line
  line `(2) Any Court trying a contravention of sub-section (1) may, without prejudice to the provisions of`
  line `section 26, direct that any rubber in respect of which the Court is satisfied that such contravention has`
  line `been committed shall be forfeited to Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (2410)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 22
  title `Licences for planting or replanting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2410&sectionno=17&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `^1[17. Licences for planting or replanting.--(1) No person shall plant or replant rubber except under`
  line `and in accodance with the conditions of a special licence issued by the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) A licence issued under this section shall specify the area in which rubber may be planted or`
  line `replanted and the period for which the licence shall be valid.`
  line
  line `(3) No licence issued under this section shall be transferable except with the land to which it relates.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 17 shall stand substituted (date to be notified) by Act 4 of 2010, s. 9 read as under:`
  line
  line `"17. Implementation of standards for quality, marking, etc., for rubber.--(1) The Board shall implement the standards`
  line `for quality, marking, labelling and packing for various marketable forms of rubber, for the rubber produced or processed in,`
  line `imported into or exported from, India.`
  line
  line `(2) Any officer of the Board authorised by the Chairman may at any reasonable time inspect the rubber sold or purchased by`
  line `any dealer or processor at any factory or other premises of a dealer, processor or manufacturer or exporter for the purpose of`
  line `ensuring the compliance of the standards under sub-section (1)."`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (2411)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 23
  title `Reports to be submitted by licencees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Section 18 shall stand omitted (date to be notified) by s. 10, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2411&sectionno=18&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `^1[18. Reports to be submitted by licencees.--(1) Every holder of a licence issued under section 17`
  line `shall, at such times as the Board may require, furnish to it a report specifying the areas newly planted or`
  line `replanted during the period to which the report relates and containing such other particulars as may be`
  line `required by the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may revoke any licence issued under section 17, if it is satisfied that the licence was`
  line `obtained by misrepresentation or fraud or if the licence contravenes any of the terms of the licence or if`
  line `the licence fails to submit the report referred to in sub-section (1).]`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (2412)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 24
  title `Fees for special licences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. The words and figures shall stand substituted (date to be notified) by s. 11, ibid., to read as "or section 15".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2412&sectionno=19&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Board may levy such fees as may be prescribed for the issue and`
  line `renewal of special licences under section 14, ^1[section 15 or section 17].`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (2413)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 25
  title `Submission of returns and maintenance of accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1954, s. 16, for clause (c) (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2413&sectionno=20&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such exceptions as may be`
  line `prescribed, every owner, every manufacturer, and every holder of a special licence issued under section`
  line `14 not being an owner or a manufacturer, shall--`
  line
  line `(a) submit to the Board, such returns at such times, in such form, and containing such particulars,`
  line `as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) maintain true and correct accounts and other records pertaining to his estate or business, as the`
  line `case may be, in such form as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `^1[(c) permit any person authorized in this behalf by the Central Government or by the Board or`
  line `any member of the Board authorized by the Chairman in writing or any officer of the Board to inspect`
  line `the accounts and records referred to in clause (b)].`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (2414)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 26
  title `Inspection of land and premises.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2414&sectionno=21&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `^1[21. Inspection of land and premises.--Any person authorized in this behalf by the Central`
  line `Government or by the Board or any member authorized by the Chairman in writing or ^2[any officer of the`
  line `Board may] at any reasonable time inspect any place of business of a dealer or any factory or other`
  line `premises of a ^3[manufacturer, for] the purpose of verifying any statement or return submitted under this`
  line `Act or for any other purposes of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for section 21 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `2. The words in brackets shall stand substituted (date to be notified) by Act 4 of 2010, s. 12 to read as "any officer of the Board`
  line `authorized by the Chairman may".`
  line
  line `3. The words in brackets shall stand substituted (date to be notified) by s. 12, ibid., to read as "manufacturer or processor, for".`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (2415)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 27
  title `Control by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2415&sectionno=22&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) All acts of the Board shall be subject to the control`
  line `of the Central Government which may cancel, suspend or modify as it thinks fit any action taken by the`
  line Board.
  line
  line `(2) The records of the Board shall be open to inspection at all reasonable times by any officer`
  line `authorized in this behalf by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22_a:
  sectionId (2416)
  sectionNo 22A
  orderNo 28
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions to Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content
  footnotes `1. The words in brackets shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by s. 13, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2416&sectionno=22A&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[22A. Power of Central Government to issue directions to Board.--(1) Without prejudice to the`
  line `foregoing provisions of this Act, the Board shall, in the discharge of its functions and duties under this`
  line `Act, be bound by such directions on questions of policy as the Central Government may give in writing to`
  line `it from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall, as far as practicable, be given opportunity to express its views before`
  line `any direction is given under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government whether a question is one of the policy or not shall be`
  line final.]
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (2417)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 29
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2417&sectionno=23&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Any person aggrieved by an order of the Board refusing to issue or renew, or revoking,`
  line `a special licence under the provisions of section 14, section 15 or section 17 may, within sixty days of the`
  line `making of the order and on payment of the prescribed fee, appeal to the Central Government, and the`
  line `decision of the Central Government thereon, and subject only to such decision the order of the Board shall`
  line `be final and shall not be called in question in any Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (2418)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 30
  title `Accounts of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2418&sectionno=24&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall keep such accounts, in such manner and in such`
  line `form as may be prescribed, of all moneys received and expended by it.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall cause the accounts to be audited annually by auditors appointed by the Central`
  line `Government, and the auditors shall have the power to disallow any item of expenditure which in their`
  line `opinion has not been properly incurred under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, on the application of the Board, allow any item of expenditure`
  line `disallowed by the auditors under sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24_a:
  sectionId (2419)
  sectionNo 24A
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_a_content
  footnotes `1. Section 24 A shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by Act 4 of 2010, s. 14.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2419&sectionno=24A&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_24_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[24A. Power to delegate.--The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `direct that any power exercisable and functions performed by it under this Act may be exercised and`
  line `performed in such cases and subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the notification by`
  line `such officer or authority as may be specified therein.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (2420)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2420&sectionno=25&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, rules made under`
  line `this section may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) principles regulating the nomination of members of the Board by the Central Government`
  line `under clause (d) of sub-section (3) of section 4, and the election or nomination of the members`
  line `referred to in clauses (b) and (c) thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that before making any nomination in the exercise of its powers the Central Government`
  line `shall call for panels of names from the respective associations recognised by it of the interests`
  line `referred to in clause (d);`
  line
  line `(ii) the term of office of members of the Board, the circumstances in which and the authority`
  line `by which members may be removed and the filling of casual vacancies in the Board;`
  line
  line `(iii) the procedure to be followed at meetings of the Board and at committees thereof for the`
  line `conduct of business, and the number of members which shall form a quorum at any meeting;`
  line
  line `(iv) the maintenance by the Board of records of business transacted by the Board, and the`
  line `submission of copies thereof to the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(v) the holding of a minimum number of meetings of the Board every year;`
  line
  line `(vi) the powers of the Board, its Chairman and committees thereof with respect to the`
  line `incurring of expenditure and the powers and duties of ^2[the Executive Director,] the Rubber`
  line `Production Commissioner and the Secretary of the Board;`
  line
  line `(vii) the conditions subject to which the Board may incur expenditure outside India;`
  line
  line `(viii) the preparation of budget estimates of receipts and expenditure of the Board and the`
  line `authority by which the estimates are to be sanctioned;`
  line
  line `(ix) the maintenance of the accounts of income and expenditure of the Board and the audit of`
  line `such accounts;`
  line
  line `(x) the deposit of the funds of the Board in banks and the investment of such funds;`
  line
  line `(xi) the re-appropriation of the estimated savings from any budget head to any other budget`
  line head;
  line
  line `(xii) the conditions subject to which the Board may borrow funds;`
  line
  line `(xiii) the conditions subject to which and the manner in which contracts may be entered into`
  line `by or on behalf of the Board;`
  line
  line `(xiv) the delegation to committees or the Chairman or Vice-Chairman or members or officers`
  line `of the Board of any of the powers and duties of the Board under this Act;`
  line
  line `(xv) the staff which may be employed by the Board and the pay and allowances and leave and`
  line `other conditions of service of officers and other employees of the Board;`
  line
  line `(xvi) the travelling and other allowances of members of the Board and of committees thereof;`
  line
  line `(xvii) the purposes for which the funds of the Board may be expended;`
  line
  line `(xviii) the maintenance of the registers and other records of the Board and of its various`
  line committees;
  line
  line `(xix) the collection of any information or statistics in respect of rubber or any product of`
  line rubber;
  line
  line `^3[(xx) the form of application for registration under section 10 or the cancellation of such`
  line `registration, the fee payable on such applications, the procedure to be followed in granting or`
  line `cancelling registration and the registers to be kept by the Board;]`
  line
  line `^4[(xxa) the cases and circumstances in which the duty of excise under section 12 shall be`
  line `payable by the owner and the manufacturers respectively, the manner in which the duty may be`
  line `assessed, paid or collected, the regulation of the production, manufacture, transport or sale of`
  line `rubber in so far as such regulation is necessary for the proper levy, payment or collection of the`
  line duty;]
  line
  line `^5[(xxb) the cost of collection and the rate of interest to be recovered in case of delayed`
  line `payment of duty under sub-section (3) of section 12;]`
  line
  line `(xxi) the form of application for special licences under section 14 ^6[or section 17], the fees for`
  line `the grant or renewal of such licences, and the forms of such licences;`
  line
  line `(xxii) the manner in which rubber shall be graded and marketed;`
  line
  line `(xxiii) the fee payable on appeals under section 23;`
  line
  line `^7(xxiiia) the manner of holding inquiry and imposing penalty under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 26B;`
  line
  line `(xxiiib) the form and manner of preferring appeal under sub-section (2) of section 26B;`
  line
  line `(xxiv) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^8[(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in ^9[two successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session in which it is so laid or the`
  line `session immediately following,] both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses`
  line `agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or`
  line `be of no effect, as the case may be, so however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule].]`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 54 of 1954, s. 18, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `2 The words in brackets shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by s. 6, ibid.`
  line
  line `3. Clause (xx) shall stand omitted (date to be notified) by Act 4 of 2010, s. 15.`
  line
  line `4 Ins. by Act 21 of 1960, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-11-1960).`
  line
  line `5. The words in brackets shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by Act 4 of 2010, s. 15.`
  line
  line `6. The words and figures "or section 17" shall stand omitted (date to be notified) by s. 15, ibid.`
  line
  line `7.Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 9-8-2024).`
  line
  line `8 Subs. by Act 21 of 1960, s. 3, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-11-1960).`
  line
  line `9 The word in brackets shall stand substituted (date to be notified) by Act 54 of 1982, s. 6 to read as "two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive`
  line `sessions aforesaid".`
obj_root_law_sections_25_a:
  sectionId (2421)
  sectionNo 25A
  orderNo 33
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content
  footnotes `1. The words in brackets shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by Act 4 of 2010, s. 16.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2421&sectionno=25A&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[25A. Power to make regulations.--(1) The Board may, with the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government, by notification make regulations, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act and the`
  line `rules made thereunder, to carry out its functions.`
  line
  line `(2) Every regulation made under sub-section (1) shall be laid before each House of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (2422)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 34
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2422&sectionno=26&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] If any person--`
  line
  line `(a) contravenes any provision of this Act, other than section 11 or section 13, or any rule made`
  line `under this Act, or`
  line
  line `(b) in any report or return to be furnished under this Act, makes any statement which is false and`
  line `which he knows to be false or does not believe to be true, or`
  line
  line `(c) obstructs any officer of the Board in the discharge of any duty imposed on or entrusted to him`
  line `by or under this Act, or`
  line
  line `(d) having the control or custody of any account book or other record, fails to produce such book`
  line `or record when required by any authorised officer to do so,`
  line
  line `he shall be ^2[liable to penalty which may extend to fifty thousand rupees.]`
  line
  line `^3[(2) If the person committing any offence under sub-section (1) is a company, every person who at`
  line `the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible to, the company for the`
  line `conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to be guilty of the`
  line `offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), where an offence under sub-section (1)`
  line `has been committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent`
  line `or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director or manager, secretary or`
  line `other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) "company", means any body corporate, and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director" in relation to a firm means a partner in the firm.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 26 renumbered as sub-section (1) of thereof by Act 54 of 1954, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for certain words (w.e.f. 9-8-2024).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 54 of 1954, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-8-1955).`
obj_root_law_sections_26_a:
  sectionId (2423)
  sectionNo 26A
  orderNo 35
  title `Compounding of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_a_content
  footnotes `1. The words in brackets shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by Act 4 of 2010, s. 18.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2423&sectionno=26A&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_26_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[26A. Compounding of offences.--Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), any offence punishable under this Act may, either before the institution of`
  line `prosecution or with the permission of the Court after the institution of the prosecution, be compounded by`
  line `the Board on payment to the Board such sum of money as does not exceed the value of the goods in`
  line `respect of which contravention has been committed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_b:
  sectionId (92538)
  sectionNo 26B
  orderNo 36
  title `Adjudication of penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 9-8-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=92538&sectionno=26B&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_26_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[26B. Adjudication of penalties.—(1) For the purposes of adjudging the penalties under`
  line `sub-section (3) of Section 11 and Section 26, the Executive Director shall appoint the Secretary to the`
  line `Board or any other officer authorised by the Central Government, as the case may be, to be an`
  line `adjudicating officer for holding an inquiry and imposing penalty in the manner as may be prescribed, after`
  line `giving any person concerned a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever is aggrieved by any order of the adjudicating officer may prefer an appeal to the`
  line `Executive Director, within a period of sixty days from the date of receipt of such order in such form and`
  line `manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) An appeal may be admitted after the expiry of the period of sixty days if the appellant satisfies the`
  line `Executive Director that he had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within that period.`
  line
  line `(4) No appeal shall be disposed of unless the appellant has been given a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard.`
  line
  line `(5) An appeal under sub-section (2) shall be disposed of within sixty days from the date of filing.`
  line
  line `(6) The amount of penalty imposed under sub-section (1), if not paid, may be recovered as an arrear`
  line `of land revenue]`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (2424)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 37
  title `Procedure for prosecutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2424&sectionno=27&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution for any offence punishable under this Act shall be`
  line `instituted except by or with the consent of the Central Government or the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27_a:
  sectionId (2425)
  sectionNo 27A
  orderNo 38
  title `Jurisdiction of Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 54 of 1954, s. 20.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2425&sectionno=27A&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_27_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[27A. Jurisdiction of Courts.--No Court inferior to that of a Presidency Magistrate or of`
  line `Magistrate of the first class shall try any offence punishable under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (2426)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 39
  title `Bar of legal proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195&sectionId=2426&sectionno=28&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00003_194724_1517807319195
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution of other legal proceedings shall lie against the`
  line `Board or any officer of the Board for anything in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
